Moroccan Linguini

1/2 c canola oil
5 garlic cloves, thinly sliced
1 jalapeno - stemmed, seeded and thinly sliced
1" piece ginger, peeled and minced
1 tbsp ground tumeric
1 tbsp ground cumin
1/4 c celery leaves, roughly chopped
2 plum tomatoes, diced
1 medium carrot, diced
1 medium white onion, diced
1 small red onion, diced
1 c dry chickpeas, soaked overnight and drained
1 c freekeh, soaked overnight and drained
8 c vegetable stock
4 c water
kosher salt and freshly ground black pepper to taste
6 tbsp fresh lemon juice
1 lb dry linguine pasta
1 c roughly chopped cilantro + more for garnish

In a 6 quart pot, heat the canola oil over medium high heat. Add the garlic, jalapeno, and ginger, and cook until lightly golden, 2 min. Stir in the tumeric and cumin, and cook until fragrant, 30 s. Add the celery leaves, tomatoes, cattor, and onions. Saute the vegetables until tender and lightly golden, 12-14 min. Add the chickpeas and freekeh, and cover with vegetable stock and water. Bring to a boil, then reduce to a simmer and cook until the chickpeas nad freekeh are tender, 1.5-2hrs. Season with salt and pepper. Add the lemon juice and dried linquine to the pot and cook, stirring occasionally, until the pasta is tender and the liquid is absorbed, 14-16 min. Stir in the chopped cilantro and season with salt and pepper. Serve, garnish with cilantro.

